In HC CDs solution, the fluorescence resonance energy transfer (FRET) may occur between the B-CDs and R-CDs. [55] The emission of the B-CDs in the visible region at 423 nm overlaps with the absorption of the R-CDs. Therefore, FRET easily occurs in the HC CDs solutions. [56] The FL lifetimes of the HC CDs and LC CDs (
Fig. S13
) are measured at 423, 493, and 586 nm to confirm the occurrence of FRET. Compared with the FL lifetimes of the LC CDs, those of the HC CDs decrease at 423 nm and increase at 493 and 586 nm, indicating that the FRET occurs between the B-CDs and R-CDs; detailed information is provided in Table S3.
